["Robert S. Capers (born July 15, 1949) is an American journalist.","Capers won the 1992 Pulitzer Prize for Explanatory Reporting with Eric Lipton for a series about the Hubble Space Telescope that illustrated many of the problems with America's space program.[1]  He worked at the Hartford Courant until 1995.[2]","This article about a United States journalist born in the 1940s is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]